HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1181
By Reneau
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Co-Responder Amanda
Finn upon her receipt of the Professional Staff
Newcomer Award.
WHEREAS, our nation was conceived by individuals who were willing to sacrifice their
personal concerns to ensure the public safety and welfare, and the Volunteer State is especially
proud to be the home of so many valiant individuals who have performed above and beyond the
call of duty in service of public safety; and
WHEREAS, one such individual is Co-Responder Amanda Finn, who was recently
honored with the Chattanooga Police Department (CPD) Professional Staff Newcomer Award,
in recognition of her exceptional performance in her role; and
WHEREAS, in less than three years, Amanda Finn has made a significant impact on the
Crisis Co-Response Unit, bringing to the team innovative ideas from her prior experience in
Colorado; and
WHEREAS, Amanda Finn efficiently improved clinical practice, training, and operations;
developed a comprehensive clinician training plan; and helped secure radios for improved
safety, communication, and law enforcement integration; and
WHEREAS, as a lead Crisis Intervention Team instructor, Amanda Finn has significantly
enhanced the curriculum, improving officers' understanding of mental health and de-escalation
skills; and
WHEREAS, beyond operations, Amanda Finn has increased the visibility and credibility
of clinicians by forging strong community and peer relationships, as well as fostering
professional growth and collaboration as a trusted peer support and mentor; and
HJR1181
016026
- 1 -

WHEREAS, the innovation, leadership, and dedication provided by Co-Responder
Amanda Finn exemplifies the spirit of a professional staff newcomer and has truly made a
lasting impact on the Chattanooga Police Department; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Co-Responder Amanda Finn upon her receipt of
the Professional Staff Newcomer Award from the Chattanooga Police Department.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
